From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Sat, 2 May 2026 06:43:34 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix: emit 'down' status when all metrics fail; parallelize
 alerts resolution
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Two fixes that pair the Node SDK with the PHP one (same wire contract):

1. The 'down' status is now emitted when metrics are defined AND every
   one returned an error. The express/fastify/hono adapters already
   mapped 'down' → HTTP 503, but buildPayload() never produced that
   value, leaving the 503 branch as dead code.

   Status priority:
     - "down"     : metrics defined and ALL returned errors → HTTP 503
     - "degraded" : at least one alert with severity "critical" → 200
     - "healthy"  : default → 200

2. Alerts now resolve in parallel via Promise.all (parity with metrics
   and custom resolution). Declaration order is still preserved in the
   output array.

Test coverage added:
  - status is 'down' when all metrics fail
  - status is not 'down' when only some metrics fail
  - status is 'healthy' when no metrics defined
  - 'down' takes priority over critical alert
  - alerts preserve declaration order even when run in parallel

All 11 tests pass (6 original + 5 new). TypeScript strict-mode clean.

